.NET Core 1.0.name: DiscordMessage
.NET Core 1.0.summary: Represents a message sent in a channel within Discord.

methods.name: Equals(DiscordMessage other)
methods.summary: Determines whether the specified DiscordMessage is equal to the current message.

methods.name: Equals(object obj)
methods.summary: Determines whether the specified object is equal to the current message.

methods.name: op_Equality(DiscordMessage a, DiscordMessage b)
methods.syntax: public static bool op_Equality(DiscordMessage a, DiscordMessage b)

methods.name: op_Inequality(DiscordMessage a, DiscordMessage b)
methods.syntax: public static bool op_Inequality(DiscordMessage a, DiscordMessage b)

methods.name: Update(DiscordApiData data)

params.value: The data to update this message with.

properties.name: Attachments
properties.summary: Gets a list of all attachments in this message.

properties.name: AuthorMember
properties.summary: Gets the guild member instance of the author of this message if it was sent in a DiscordGuildChannel.

properties.name: Channel
properties.summary: Gets the channel this message is in.

properties.name: EditedTimestamp
properties.summary: Gets the time of the last edit to this message.

properties.name: Embeds
properties.summary: Gets a list of all embedded attachments in this message.

properties.name: IsPinned
properties.summary: Gets whether or not this message is pinned in the containing channel.

properties.name: MentionEveryone
properties.summary: Gets whether or not this message mentioned everyone via @everyone.

properties.name: Mentions
properties.summary: Gets a list of all user-specific mentions in this message.

properties.name: Nonce
properties.summary: Used for validating if a message was sent.

properties.name: TextToSpeech
properties.summary: Gets whether or not this message was sent with the /tts command.

properties.name: Timestamp
properties.summary: Gets the time this message was first sent.
